<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Recently Verant has told us that Charisma will help in determining your chances of LANDING a mez/charm on a player. In actual practice this is NOT the case at all, in fact it appears Charisma does NOTHING in aiding these spells. The mez/Charm line of spells is wholly dependent on the targets Magic resistence, no ammout of charisma will help you land. Lets look at the results of a recent test between me (A lvl 50 Enchanter, vs a lvl 50 Necromancer.<P>Stats that are of importance here.<BR>Enchanter:<BR>Cha-204<P>Necromancer:<BR>Magic Resistence of 167<BR>(The necromancer I speak of has 2 Plat Jacinth Rings, Crown of King Tranix etc, I added Group Magic Resistence to bring his MR up to this unbelievable lvl)<BR>As a added note, the Necromancer has a Wisdom of 67. This is important because in Verant's Offical players guide it is stated on page 79-80 that "It is also involved in resisting magical spells that effect the mind." Even though I dont believe that wisdom does anything of the sort, I felt a need to state his wisdom for the record.<P>Test was performed in the Arena in Lake Rathe. A arena environment was important due to the fact this is the only place you can charm a PC.<P>In 10 casts of lvl 49 Dazzle. Supposedly a very diffucult mez line spell to resist due to its high lvl.<BR>10 resists.<P>10 casts of lvl 49 Allure. <BR>10 resists.<P>I removed ALL my charisma items and brought my charisma down to its base lvl of 90.<BR>The necromancer removed all his Magic resistence items to bring his MR down to its base of 25.<P>10 casts of dazzle.<BR>9 spells landed successfully.<P>10 casts of Allure.<BR>8 spells landed successfully.<P>I put back on my charisma gear to see if I could go for a perfect run of landing the spells. Charisma back to 204.<P>10 casts of Dazzle.<BR>7 laned successfully<P>10 casts of Allure.<BR>7 landed successfully.<P>This time I casted Tashania on him before I attempted to Dazzle/Allure him. This brought his MR into the negative numbers. (negative 8 magic resistence to be exact) My charisma is still 204.<P>10 casts of Dazzle<BR>9 landed successfully<P>10 casts of Allure.<BR>7 landed Successfully.<P>I took my charisma items off again to base lvl of 90. The necromancer was tash'd. His mr is still negative 8.<P>10 casts of dazzle.<BR>10 landed successfully.<P>10 casts of allure.<BR>8 landed successfully.<P>It appears that Verant doesnt have its facts straight. As of right now, Charisma does nothing to help the Enchanter with his spells. I suppose it doesnt help the Bard either but who knows. <P>Magic resistence is the only thing that will allow a enchanter to successfully LAND his spell. We have a high lvl, quested for Magic debuff in Tashania but unfortuneatly it doesnt lower MR NEARLY enough to help on high lvl mobs. In actual game play, mobs in the planes are very difficult to charm or mez. There are a few exceptions. Undead seem to charm and mez the easiest. I dont know the stats on these mobs but if Verant were to look at thier Magic resistence I will assure you that it is much lower then the other mobs that frequent the planes.<P>Kreuzius level 50 Enchanter Fennin Ro<P><p>[This message has been edited by Kreuzius MindStealer (edited 02-02-2000).]
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
