<BR>Let me humbly suggest the placebo effect: We add all this charisma gear, and convince ourselves that it makes a huge difference, when, in fact, it makes none at all or only a marginal one.<P>Crazy? Remember how convinced people were about dexterity until we finally got the truth about that?<P>After that episode, I take everything verant tells me with a grain of salt.<P>I am also among those starting to question the charisma thing, wondering whether I shouldn't swap back the int i gave up.<P>I suppose it is possible there is a difference between pvp and pve in this regard, but I doubt it. Anyway, that could be tested too. Just cast a blue pet and have someone root it over and over while you mez it over and over. You can turn it into an npc first, if i remember right, by mem bluring, if that makes a difference.<P>tatianna is right tho. You should have changed only one variable (charisma), not two (charisma and MR). In support of the original post, I did a similar test once - one variable at a time - with a higher level druid friend, and found charisma had no impact while magic resist had a huge one.<P><P>------------------<BR>Nong Ninnipus<BR>40th Enchanter<P>
