After thinking about this, I have to agree that my test was fundamentaly flawed. I was testing vs. a player instead of vs a mob. I will conduct the same test vs Guard Jendl (without killing him so I know his lvl is constent). I will also test charm length even though Verant has stated this is a random number. I am however absolutely convinced that cha will not help if mr is already high enough. We were told by Verent that it does help but Verant's track record for distributing correct information is sketchy to say the least. One glaring example is the use of Dexterity for casters. Verant had posted that dexterity does NOT help a caster regain concentration when hit while casting a spell. Now let me quote Verant's Offical Players Guide about the use of Dexterity. Page 79...."Dexterity (DEX): This is your hand/eye coordination and is used in combat accuracy and spell casting capability. This is used in calculation your missle combat skill and aids in determining if you are interrupted when you are hit while casting a spell." I know I'm getting off the subject here, but the point of my whole post is that either a. Verant doesnt know how the skills and spells work on the real servers or b. They are assuming how they work without actual testing. In the past 'B' seems to come up more often then not. I am trying to do a little of my own testing to make sure I'm not wasting slots for charisma items that could better be used for things like dex gear.<P>Kreuzius
