<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Well the topic is flawed, we do know that Charisma up until about 105 I think it is effects the price you get at a vendor. <P>Apart from that, I'm not sure about it. From my own experience, things tend to work better for me the higher my charisma gets. I'm an erudite enchanter who dumped all of my points in INT, to 142 natural, and the rest I put in CHA which I believe is 90 on it's own. Now I'm level 25 and with items and buffing I'm at 166 int 150 charisma.<P>Charisma is such a cheap stat to increase. What other stat can you raise so high? Gold cats eye bracelets? + 7 cha each... I picked up for 30pp for a pair. Crude Stein, + 15 cha? They practically give them away around oggok. <P>Then there's Sympathetic Aura and the higher level versions of the spell... a charisma buff that's cheap. <P>Now my thought is, if Charisma was *THAT* important, why is it so easy to get more of? <P>From my own experience, from level 20 to about 22 I soloed the 2 spawn cove in Lake Rathetear. There are two birds that spawn up in a birdhouse. If I waited too long and had to break up the spawn, I pulled them down one at a time by casting mez on the bird in the front, that would aggro the other bird on me who would come trotting down at which point my pet and I would proceed to pound him in the ground. What I did notice, was that if I failed to cast Sympathetic Aura on myself, then I felt I was resisted more.<P>Keep in mind, these birds always spawned blue to me, but they are not always the same level. Perhaps I was fooled by different spawn levels, I don't know.<P>Though I will make one other point, lately I have been spending a lot of time in Cazic Thule. The fascinating part is, when my friends and I decided to take the pyramid, my spells seemed to be resisted <ul>less</ul> by the yellows and reds to me (27-30) then they were by the evens and blues. It seems lately, whenever I come across a blue they are resisting my stuns more often than the reds were, and this seems the same with/without tashani.<P>About the only disheartening thing about fighting at the pyramid was that our druid was pulling because harmony works BETTER than our series of lulls. That kinda irks me.<P>Bene Incantatore<BR>25th Enchanter of Quellious<BR>Brell Serilis
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="1"  face="Verdana, Arial">
 Posts: <B></B>  &nbsp;|&nbsp; IP: <A HREF="http://forums.crgaming.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=get_ip&f=9&t=000601&reply_num=000032">Logged</A>
</FONT>
</td></tr>
</table>
</td></tr>

